  <prompt>
    Close ledger entry RB-T012-01 by repairing `SessionRestoreService.NormaliseETag` and `SessionRestoreService.ExtractODataETag` in
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionRestoreService.cs`. Both helpers mishandle quote characters in OData/JSON ETag values:

    - `NormaliseETag` uses `etag.Trim('"')` which strips ALL leading and trailing `"` chars (over-strips embedded quotes).
    - `ExtractODataETag` calls `IndexOf('"', start)` which stops at the FIRST JSON-escaped `\"` and returns a truncated value.

    Production fix per ledger Recommended Fix section:
    - `NormaliseETag` MUST strip at most one matched outer `"` pair only (e.g., regex `^"(.*)"$` or manual length-check substring).
    - `ExtractODataETag` MUST handle JSON escape sequences (recommend `System.Text.Json.JsonDocument.Parse(...).RootElement.GetProperty("@odata.etag").GetString()`).

    Test impact: 2 Skip'd tests (`NormaliseETag_StripsOuterQuotes` Theory with 2 inline cases + `ExtractODataETag_FindsETagInJsonBody` Fact) flip Skip -> Pass.
    Per NFR-04: commit message MUST cite "RB-T012-01" + resolution mode `repaired`.
  </prompt>

  <role>BFF production-fix engineer closing a LOW-severity real-bug ledger entry under repair-not-rewrite discipline.</role>

  <goal>
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionRestoreService.cs` updated so that:
    - `NormaliseETag` returns the value with at most one matched leading+trailing `"` pair stripped (preserves embedded quotes).
    - `ExtractODataETag` parses the JSON body via `System.Text.Json` (or equivalent escape-aware approach) and returns the unescaped `@odata.etag` value.

    Two Skip'd tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionRestoreServiceTests.cs` have their `Skip = "..."` attributes removed
    and class-level `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` applies. All tests pass. Ledger entry RB-T012-01 row updated with fix-commit SHA + status `repaired`.
  </goal>

