  <context>
    <background>
      Per r1 ledger entry RB-T012-01 (filed 2026-05-31, fix-by 2026-07-31): both helpers preserve end-to-end staleness detection because saved and current ETags are processed identically by the broken normalization. The unit tests on the helpers individually surface the bugs. The HTTP-header path uses raw values without JSON escapes; `ExtractODataETag` is only hit when the header is absent.

      The minimal repair: replace `Trim('"')` with an outer-pair check; replace the substring scan with `JsonDocument.Parse`. Keep API signatures unchanged. Re-enable the 2 Skip'd tests; class-level `[Trait("status","repaired")]` automatically applies.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="029" status="must-be-complete">Phase 2 exit triple-run validation (zero failures) before Phase 3 starts</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
